<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <style>
            div{
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                background-color: red;
                position: relative;
                animation-name: example;
                animation-duration: 4s;
                animation-iteration-count: infinite;
            }
            @keyframes example{
                0% {background-color: red;left: 0px;top: 0px;}
                25% {background-color:rebeccapurple;left: 200px;top: 0px;}
                50% {background-color: goldenrod;left: 200px;top: 200px;}
                75% {background-color: fuchsia;left: 0px;top: 200px;}
                100% {background-color: tan;left: 0px;top: 0px;}
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1> css animation </h1>
        <p> the animation-iteration-count property can be set  to infinite to let the animation run for ever: </p>
        <div> </div>
    </body>
</html>
